Name one virus/worm in the last 5 years that came out and exploited machines *before* the vulnerability was disclosed.  Hell, name me one that exploited machines before the fix was released.<br>
<br>
As for relying on firewalls, yes, firewalls are good.  Having firewalls and patching your machine is better.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, security isn't some binary switch you turn on or off.  It's basically a layer after layer after layer of obstacles that keep malicious twits out of your system.  <br>
<br>
With just a firewall and an unpatched machine, your only line of defense is that firewall.  If I can find a way to circumvent it, your machine can be exploited.  And no, I don't have to attack your firewall directly.  Hell, even firewalls can have flaws in their code allowing for remote attacks.  However, if you have a firewall and a patched machine, not only would I have to get through your firewall, I would also have to find a different vulnerability on your machine to exploit it.<br>
<br>
The more layers you create, the better the security model.  Ideally, we would create an ungodly number of layers protecting every single byte of data.  Unfortunately, that tends to become expensive and unmanageable very quickly.  So the end result is a compromise.  In most cases, the cost of patching your machine is very low relative to the benefit it provides. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shehbahn>shehbahn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No blood for oil!</span><br>  Posts: 1240<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/19/03 1:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New avenue of attack for Win 2000K and XP</span><hr size=1> On top of my head, though i certainly dont remember the chronology : when were the Lovebug / Melissa flaws announced ? Before or after MS disclosed it ?<br>
