<br>
For the other drive partitions, drill down through the Disk Management snap in.  You'll see the option of mounting partitions to specific mount points rather than drive letters.  Combine this with DFS and you have pretty much the same thing as any network based file system under Unix.  Infact, my workstation has three harddrives, it however has only one DOS drive partition--drive C.  All other partitions are mounted off directories off C.<br>
